Baltika Brewery Climbs Most in 2 Months on Buyback Plan

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-04-28T15:15:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/baltika-brewery-climbs-most-in-month-on-share-buyback-plan.html
Baltika Brewery (PKBA)  gained the most in
two months after the company said it plans to buy back as much
as 5 percent of its stock for a maximum of 11.5 billion rubles
($418 million).  The shares surged 7.9 percent, the biggest gain since Feb.
25, to 1,354.50 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow.  The Russian brewery is offering 1,407 rubles a common share
and 1,286 rubles a preferred shares, the company said today in
an e-mailed statement. 